`Dog` doesn&#39;t define a toString method, and the default toString method just returns the class name and the hashCode of the object. You just need to make a new method inside `Dog` looking like this:
```java
@Override // &lt;- technically optional, but very recommended
public String toString() {
    return &quot;What you want to show up when printing a Dog&quot;;
}
```

Anything returned in this method will show up when printing a `Dog`, you can make the returned value anything you&#39;d like. Returning null will probably cause issues at some point tho, so don&#39;t do that.

